      "name": "Adventorial Article",
      "settings": {
        "title": "",
        "subtitle": "1. One Watch For Work, One For Life",
        "image": "shopify://shop_images/Frame_1984078502_2.webp",
        "content": "<p>You don’t want to gamble your Apple Watch every time you clock in.<br/><br/>When you’re walking into a job site, shop, warehouse, yard, or cab, you know what’s coming: hits, scrapes, sparks, grease, dust, and stuff falling where it shouldn’t. That environment isn’t friendly to thin glass and a polished case.<br/><br/>This is where a work watch steps in. You keep your Apple Watch for what it’s great at—clean days, nights out, family time, weekends. And you let <a href=\"/products/carbinox-blaze\" title=\"Carbinox Blaze Smartwatch – Ultimate Pack\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><strong>the Carbinox Blaze</strong></span></a> take over when it’s time to get your hands filthy.<br/><br/>You strap on the work watch when the boots go on, so your Apple Watch doesn’t get blasted by everything your job throws at you. Same wrist, different watch, and a lot less stress about smashing something expensive on a lift, frame rail, or beam.<br/><br/></p>",
